Pakuapatitit Atemmohara,
Danced with the wind beneath a bright star.
Over the hills and across the sea,
Chasing the echoes of a singing tree.

The moon wore silver upon its face,
While fireflies painted the night with grace.
Pakuapatitit laughed with delight,
Gathering dreams in the velvet night.

Atemmohara, bold and free,
Whispered secrets to every leaf and tree.
And when the dawn awoke the sky,
Their songs still lingered, drifting by.

So if you wander where wild winds play,
You may hear their melody someday—
Pakuapatitit Atemmohara's tune,
Dancing from sunrise to the moon. 🌙✨
